description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, motivated health care support worker to join our busy outpatient’s teams at Prince Charles and Ysbyty Cwm Cynon.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is permanent, full time 37.5 hours per week, worked over 5 days .The successful post holder will be required and able to work across both sites but will have a base at PCH.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will involve caring for patients within a wide range of specialities including ophthalmology, dermatology, surgery and medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must be able to work as part of a team and have good communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The main role is to support trained nurses and medical staff in delivery of high standards of care and to assist and support patients through a varied range of investigations and treatments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is desirable but not essential to have outpatients experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sister Deborah Evans&lt;br /&gt;Outpatients Department&lt;br /&gt;Tel: 01685 728103- Prince Charles Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deborah.evans4@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
